  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hope to get by reduced and delayed acute radiodermatitis following the
      application of dressings to skin hydrogel Hydrosorb®, a reduction in head and neck pains and
      improved quality of life of patients with head and neck cancer treated with concomitant
      radiotherapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
